Fast Negative Embedding

Token mix of my usual negative embedding. This way it's faster to use and easier to reproduce.

I'm also working on a much stronger one that doesn't preserve styles but it's good on base models without style loras applied. I plan to upload it during the next week, so be sure to leave a ❤️ to be notified of future updates.

This is very much a work in progress, but since I'm already using it in examples, I thought I should upload it.

It should keep styles on all my style loras. If not please tell me in the comments.

Of course, don't use this in the positive prompt.
This includes Nerf's Negative Hand embedding.

Alexandra Botez

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

Alexandra Botez is a Canadian chess player and streamer, and the older sister of Andrea Botez.

Update: Retrained from scratch, as this was a very old TI and my process has changed quite a bit since I created it. I think the previous version was good, but probably not as accurate as I would have desired. This new version resembles Alexandra more, I would say. I'm not totally convinced with her hair tonality, but that's easily fixable through prompting. I might revise the dataset in the future to try to solve the issue, but there's just not much good material online of hers, unfortunately.

This version is a 1500-step TI trained on a dataset of 18 images with my usual settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (4l3xbotez:0.99), a woman with black hair, RAW, close portrait photo, long brown coat, turtleneck, long haircut, slim body, (high detailed skin:1.2), 8k uhd, dslr, soft lighting, high quality, film grain, Fujifilm XT3 sharp focus, f 5.6"

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

USSR style (embedding)

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

❗v1 = 10 tokens❗

❗v2 = 20 tokens❗ !The version has almost no effect, I use ussrv3!

❗v3 = 35 tokens❗

Rus (below in english)

Приветствую, товарищи, эта модель создана для генерации анимешных или полу-анимешных артов около советской тематики, она хорошо работает с чекпоинтами RevAnimated и AOM3, а вот deliberate выдаёт слабенькие 2д постеры.

Не стесняйтесь добавлять более подробное описание

У модели есть три версии: USSR, USSRv2 и USSRv3.

👇🏻👇🏽👇🏿

Первая модель обучена на 10 векторах, вторая на 20, а третья на 35. То есть v1 не всегда лучше v2 или v3!

Соответствующее количество токенов они будут занимать. Результаты у них схожи но я бы предпочёл USSRv3, также я пробовал ставить 75 векторов но результат мне показался неудовлетворительным и я даже не стал заливать это сюда.

Если вы знаете как улучшить этот эмбединг обязательно напишите в коментах! В дальнейшем я продолжу изучать токены сея тематики и соответственно обновлять модель.

Eng

Greetings comrades, this model is created to generate anime or half-anime art around Soviet themes, it works well with RevAnimated and AOM3 checkpoints, but gives weak 2d posters with Deliberate.

The model has three versions: USSR, USSRv2 and USSRv3.

👇🏻👇🏽👇🏿

The first model is trained on 10 vectors, the second on 20, and the third on 35. The corresponding number of tokens they will occupy. The results are similar but I would have preferred USSRv3, I also tried to put 75 vectors but I found the result unsatisfactory and didn't even upload it here.

If you know how to improve this embedding be sure to write in the comments! In the future I will continue to study the tokens of this theme and update the model accordingly.

Тэги: sovietussrсссрstylecommunism
Токены: ussr
SHA256: 03605741B97D3BF1F88D64AB93D3213A01A7ADC6573A38CC7714598643384174
